  "prompt": "Does it hurt to get stitches removed?",
  "response": "Getting stitches removed typically does not hurt, although some people may experience minor discomfort or a slight pinch during the process. The area around the stitches may be sensitive, especially if it\u2019s healing, but the procedure itself is usually quick and straightforward. If you have concerns about pain or sensitivity, it's a good idea to discuss them with your healthcare provider before the removal. They can provide guidance on what to expect and how to manage any discomfort.",
